<font color="#FF0000">ATTENTION VIETNAM VETS</font><br>
<tt>Tue Mar  4  1:25:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
One of the reasons Vietnam will never go away is because it's unfinished business.  No I don't mean we should go back.  I mean we began a &quot;good&quot; work and didn't finish it.  We put everything we had into Vietnam and came up short.  The life that is in us has an indigenous aspiring nature.  Our very nature was violated in Nam.  Most of us by now have transfered those hopes to our kids, wives, possessions or whatever.  But in order to transcend or be creative we must find another goal as worthwhile as we thought our goal was in Nam.  Any suggestions?  
